==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enshrine
<hw>En*shrine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Enshrined</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Enshrining</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To inclose in a
shrine or chest; hence, to preserve or cherish as something sacred;
<as>as, to <ex>enshrine</ex> something in memory</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We will <qex>enshrine</qex> it as holy relic.</q>
<rj><qau>Massinger.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enshroud</ent>⟦br⟧
